theorem Topology.P1_compl_of_isClosed_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h_closed : IsClosed (A : Set X)) (h_open : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) (Aᶜ : Set X) := by
  -- The complement of a clopen set is itself clopen.
  have h_closed_compl : IsClosed (Aᶜ : Set X) := h_open.compl
  have h_open_compl  : IsOpen (Aᶜ : Set X) := h_closed.compl
  -- Apply the existing lemma for clopen sets to the complement.
  simpa using
    Topology.P1_of_isClosed_isOpen
      (X := X) (A := (Aᶜ : Set X)) h_closed_compl h_open_compl

theorem IsOpen.compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {s : Set X}
    (h : IsOpen (s : Set X)) :
    IsClosed ((s : Set X)ᶜ) := by
  simpa using h.isClosed_compl

theorem IsClosed.compl {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {s : Set X}
    (h : IsClosed (s : Set X)) :
    IsOpen ((s : Set X)ᶜ) := by
  simpa using h.isOpen_compl
